{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"4120421c-8c09-4c1e-82b8-97d88c7489f3","content":"No repo-specific pipeline files found, so here's general guidance:\n\n## Migrating from VSTest@3 to Microsoft.Testing.Platform\n\n**1. Update your test project** — add the MTP runner:\n\n```xml\n<PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.Testing.Platform.MSBuild\" Version=\"1.*\" />\n```\n\nand set:\n\n```xml\n<EnableMSTestRunner>true</EnableMSTestRunner>\n<OutputType>Exe</OutputType>\n```\n\n**2. Replace `VSTest@3` with `dotnet test`** in your pipeline:\n\n```yaml\n# Before\n- task: VSTest@3\n  inputs:\n    testAssemblyVer2: '**/*Tests.dll'\n    resultsFolder: $(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults\n    codeCoverageEnabled: true\n\n# After\n- task: DotNetCoreCLI@2\n  displayName: 'Run tests'\n  inputs:\n    command: test\n    projects: '**/*Tests.csproj'\n    arguments: >-\n      --logger \"trx;LogFileName=results.trx\"\n      --results-directory $(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults\n      --collect \"Code Coverage\"\n```\n\n**3. Publish results & coverage:**\n\n```yaml\n- task: PublishTestResults@2\n  condition: always()\n  inputs:\n    testResultsFormat: VSTest\n    testResultsFiles: '$(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults/**/*.trx'\n\n- task: PublishCodeCoverageResults@2\n  inputs:\n    summaryFileLocation: '$(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults/**/*.cobertura.xml'\n```\n\n**Key differences:**\n- Tests now run as executables via `dotnet test`, not via the VSTest runner scanning DLLs.\n- TRX and coverage are requested via CLI arguments instead of task inputs.\n- Use `PublishTestResults@2` + `PublishCodeCoverageResults@2` as separate steps (VSTest@3 bundled these).","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"f4aa136a-612f-4862-b2f5-ee1e12d84b4a","outputTokens":482,"requestId":"CFCA:2D9C3A:602EF5D:6B6190F:69EC0EA6"},"id":"7c4a3c82-d2fc-4620-9d75-c08bd61bc207","timestamp":"2026-04-25T00:45:36.287Z","parentId":"52cd75ec-4faa-4ecd-bd06-db3f3e0cf6db"}
